<HEADLINE>
<P>
BATTLING THE MEDFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County will conduct aerial spraying of malathion tonight. 
</P>
<P>
Area: 22 square miles encompassing South Pasadena and parts of San Marino, 
Monterey Hills, El Sereno and Alhambra. 
</P>
<P>
Time: 9 p.m. to 3 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Precautions: Stay indoors; keep animals indoors; wash animal dishes and toys 
left outside; cover cars; keep doors and windows closed. 
</P>
<P>
Information: Toll-free numbers for the agricultural commissioner: (800) 
356-2894; (800) 225-1346. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Map, BATTLING THE MEDFLY, GEORGE CAREY / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
