<P>
MORNING REPORT: SPLITSVILLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIEL CERONE , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Basinger Case Takes a Twist: There are probably a few Hollywood celebrities 
with more than a casual interest in the divorce case of sultry Kim Basinger, 
one of the hottest stars of the past few years, and her soon-to-be ex-husband, 
Ron Britton. The two start negotiations next week leading to a divorce 
agreement, and the New York Daily News reports that Britton is threatening to 
take the case to trial, where he says he will name men romantically involved 
with his wife if Basinger does not give him a multimillion-dollar settlement. 
Basinger, who has never been shy about her life style, has been linked with 
"Batman" co-star Michael Keaton, producer Jon Peters and rock star Prince, 
among others. DANIEL CERONE 
</P>
