<TEXT>
<P>
WRKO radio has selected Bob Starr, play-by-play announcer for the Angels, to 
succeed Ken Coleman as the Red Sox principal radio broadcaster next season, 
according to John Carlson, another sports broadcaster at the station. 
</P>
<P>
Starr's broadcasting career spans more than 30 years, including 18 years with 
major league baseball. Starr also did play-by-play announcing of the New 
England Patriots and Boston College football from 1966 to 1970 on WBZ radio. 
Part of that time was spent as sports anchor at WBZ-TV. 
