<HEADLINE>
<P>
N.Y. SUBWAY TRAIN HITS 2 MEN, KILLING THEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two young men were struck by a train and killed early Tuesday, apparently as 
they were writing graffiti, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Cans of spray paint were found near the bodies at the 59th Street subway 
station, Transit Police Officer Joseph Ciociola said. The victims were about 50 
feet south of a waiting platform. 
</P>
<P>
The train's motorman said he did not see the men as he pulled into the station, 
but the train braked automatically upon impact, Ciociola said. 
</P>
