<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 24 ARRESTED IN SWEEP OF BAD-CHECK SUSPECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A two-day sweep by district attorney's investigators for unrepentant bad-check 
writers across the San Gabriel Valley netted at least 24 arrests, authorities 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The operation, employing about two dozen investigators armed with more than 200 
arrest warrants, was designed to publicize the District Attorney's Bad Check 
Enforcement Program, which has operated since 1986 in the San Gabriel Valley 
and is being expanded to include the city of Los Angeles. Thirteen people were 
in custody by midday Monday and by Tuesday afternoon, a total of 24 people 
either were arrested or voluntarily surrendered after finding notices of the 
warrants left at their homes, said Lt. Duane Trump of the District Attorney's 
Bureau of Investigation. 
</P>
<P>
Despite arresting only a small fraction of the people sought, Trump said the 
operation was a success. 
</P>
</TEXT>
