<TEXT>
<P>
New Construction Down 6%: New construction contracts were down 6% in October to 
$262.58 billion, compared to $279.72 billion in September, the F. W. Dodge 
construction report said. The October figures reflected the tone set in the 
industry in the past two years, and followed a strong September performance 
reflecting an unusually large number of public works projects, the report said. 
The October decline mostly reflected an 11% drop to an annualized $46.8 billion 
from $52.88 billion in September in the public works and utilities construction 
sector. Residential building held steadily in October at $121.5 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
