<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
HONG KONG WANTS REFUGEES OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONG KONG 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Legislature today passed a motion urging the forced return of Vietnamese 
refugees, and several lawmakers condemned U.S. opposition to the idea. 
</P>
<P>
The Legislative Council vote reflected the strong local sentiment to rid this 
British colony of the nearly 57,000 Vietnamese languishing in squalid detention 
centers after fleeing their communist homeland by boat. 
</P>
<P>
"Mandatory repatriation is a must, and it should have been implemented 
yesterday," lawmaker Rita Fan said during the debate. 
</P>
<P>
Some lawmakers attributed Washington's position to a "guilty conscience," a 
reference to the U.S. role in the Vietnam War. 
</P>
</TEXT>
