<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE GIRL WHO HAD BABY AT SCHOOL TO GO TO JUVENILE HALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 15-year-old girl was expected to be released from a hospital into police 
custody today, a day after she gave birth to a baby boy who was found dead 
lying face down in a toilet in a girl's high school bathroom, officers said. 
</P>
<P>
While an autopsy was conducted this morning on the baby, Garden Grove police 
said the Santiago High School honor student could face manslaughter charges or 
worse in connection with the death. 
</P>
<P>
"We'll not really know for sure what we'll do until after the autopsy," said 
Garden Grove Police Lt. Chuck Gibbs. He added that, for now, "we're handling it 
as a homicide." 
</P>
<P>
The girl, a sophomore whose name was not released because of her age, was 
arrested Tuesday for investigation of homicide. (Story, A1). The girl was taken 
to UCI Medical Center in Orange and will be booked directly at Orange County 
Juvenile Hall upon her release, Gibbs said. He said authorities fear that the 
girl may run away if released into the custody of her family, 
</P>
<P>
Santiago High School Principal Bob O'Higgins said he told the school's 1,900 
students of the tragedy this morning in brief remarks over the loudspeaker 
system. 
</P>
<P>
"Basically I explained the tragedy and that there was an ongoing investigation 
and that I appreciate how they handled the situation," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
