<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CUESTA BEATS SADDLEBACK, ADVANCES TO STATE TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cuesta College, ranked No. 3 in the state, ended Saddleback's first trip to the 
playoffs in 10 years, defeating the Gauchos, 15-6, 15-10, 15-6, Tuesday in a 
Southern California Regional women's volleyball match at Cuesta. 
</P>
<P>
Heather Mead had 27 assists, Cyndi Rhone had 11 kills and Laura Farrell had 
nine kills for Saddleback, which ended its season 16-4. Cuesta is 25-2 and 
advances to the state tournament Saturday at Citrus College in Glendora. 
</P>
<P>
In another women's volleyball Southern California Regional playoff match: 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos 3, Golden West 0 -- Maureen Flannigan had 12 kills for the Rustlers 
(15-5), but Cerritos (13-4) swept, 15-3, 15-12, 15-3. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 85, Rio Hondo 69 -- Vince Hizon, a sophomore guard from Mater Dei High 
School, made 10 of 13 shots from the field and scored 22 points for host 
Cypress. Eric Pauley, a 6-foot-10 freshman who played at Savanna High, scored 
17 points, six rebounds and six blocks for Cypress, which took a 12-0 lead. 
Cypress led at halftime, 35-25, but Rio Hondo cut the lead to 53-50 with nine 
minutes remaining to play. A layup by Hizon with about six minutes left capped 
a 12-4 run and the Chargers (5-0) weren't challenge by the Roadrunners (0-6) 
again. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 72, Moorpark 43 -- The Pirates took a 38-14 halftime lead as they 
defeated previously unbeaten Moorpark (4-1) at Orange Coast. Kami Bigler scored 
14 points, Michelle Hennessey had 10 assists and Erika Manning and Jennifer 
Ambrose each had eight rebounds for Orange Coast (6-1). 
</P>
</TEXT>
